What will it be like to work for the Hilton Worldwide Brand?One of the most recognized names in the industry, Hilton Worldwide offers travellers a world of authentic experiences. The brand continues to be the innovative, forward-thinking global leader of hospitality. With products and services that meet the needs of tomorrow's savvy global travellers, we shape experiences in which every Guest feels cared for, valued and respected.If you understand the importance of upholding a brand's reputation and value the effort it takes to provide a globally recognized hospitality experience, you may be just the person we are looking for to work as part of the Hilton Worldwide Team. Because it's with Hilton Hotels & Resorts that we promise an exceptional Guest experience every time.
What is the opportunity?
Following our successful conversion to Hilton in 2013, we are now looking for a Director of Business Development to join the team and continue the successful performance of Hilton Sharjah, a 250-bedroom hotel with 4 F&B; outlets and 190 Team Members on the outskirts of Dubai.
Leading a team of 10 and reporting directly to the General Manager, the successful candidate will be fully responsible for the performance of the 4 Business Development functions of:
1) Revenue
2) Sales
3) Conference & Events Sales
4) Marketing & Public Relations
What will I be doing?
As Director of Business Development, you will be responsible for developing a commercial strategy covering all segments and channels to maximize the revenue and profit performance of the hotel and then execute the commercial strategy through proficient management of the Revenue, Sales, Conference and Events Sales and Marketing / Public Relations teams and their activities, also working effectively with the regional and
area support teams.
Key responsibilities will include:
1) REVENUE
Delivering the optimal RGI performance
Accurate evaluation of the hotel market mix, segmentation and respective revenue forecasts
Proactive review and analysis of the Rate & Inventory strategy and results
Effective utilisation of the Revenue Management System (current RMS is IDeaS.V7)
Developing the hotel ‘Commercial Focus Matrix’ with short, medium and long-term strategies
Evaluating market demand by utilising internal and external reports, including market share, market conditions, competitive pricing etc. (current reporting systems include OnQR&I;, Cognos, SmithTravelResearch, TravelClick Rubicon and Hotelligence, etc.)
Preparing, analysing and regularly updating reports to outline business Risks and Opportunities
Preparing the Annual Revenue Plan for the hotel, its presentation and justification
Generating periodic updates on transient booking patterns
2) SALES
Managing the Sales Personnel to deliver optimal revenue and yield performance
Personally leading the negotiation of all high value, high profile and key client negotiations
Effective coordination of strategies for group sales and maximising conversion
Assisting with the account diagnostics process and validating conclusions for negotiated business and on-line sales strategies
3) C&E; SALES
Managing and guiding the C&E; Sales team to achieve all viable revenue opportunities
Personally leading the negotiation of all high value, high profile and key client C&E; negotiations
Effective utilisation of the C&E; Revenue Management System (current system is Delphi v9.5)
Developing appropriate and viable C&E; sales products to generate demand
4) MARKETING
Managing the local Marketing programme of the hotel, the annual marketing plan and its respective activities
Managing the Social Media operations of the hotel including Revinate, TripAdvisor, Facebook, booking.com, hotels4u.com etc.
Managing local Public Relations and communications strategies and drafting Press Releases in accordance with Hilton policies
OTHER
Recruiting, managing, training and developing the best possible Business Development Team
Developing all Business Development Team Members in their Revenue Management skills, their Sales strategies and techniques, their C&E; Sales competencies and their Marketing outlook to the business
Setting, monitoring and evaluating the Key Business Objective of each member of the BD Team to render their best possible performance
Constant coaching of all members of the BD Team along the paths of their Personal Development Plans to ensure their best possible career progression
Who are we looking for?
A Director of Business Development serving Hilton is always working on behalf of our Guests and working with other Team Members. To successfully fill this role, you should maintain the attitude, behaviours, skills, and values that follow:
Excellent oral and written communication skills
Ability to communicate, verbal and in written form, effectively with Management and Ownership groups
Excellent organisation skills
Ability to work well under time pressure
Excellent interpersonal skills and a full understanding of professional ethics, decorum and social skills required for extensive interaction with customers, investment owners and business partners
Ability to perform critical analysis
Strong experience in hospitality forecasting, pricing and inventory control
Strong leadership skills to effectively manage and motivate a high-performing team positioned to exceed targets
Strong analytical skills to understand key business indicators and competitive trends and develop approaches to these challenges
Excellent selling capabilities and the ability and desire to coach selling techniques to Team Members
It would be advantageous in this position for you to demonstrate the following capabilities and distinctions:
Knowledge of the hotel property management systems
Significant experience in revenue management or a similar analytical role
Relevant associate degree, in business development or other relevant business field, from an academic institution
The successful candidate is likely to exhibit strong Team Player Skills, Emotional Intelligence and Cultural Awareness.
